Bigscreen Beyond / Beyond 2 display support (DRM/EDID + amdgpu DSC bpp)

Rebased onto Linux 7.0.9 for Rustlux from the upstream series by
Yaroslav Bolyukin <iam@lach.pw> (bigscreen-beyond-kernel-7.0.12.patch,
https://lore.kernel.org/all/20251202110218.9212-1-iam@lach.pw/):

  1/7 drm/edid: rename VESA block parsing functions to more generic name
  2/7 drm/edid: prepare for VESA vendor-specific data block extension
  3/7 drm/edid: MSO should only be used for non-eDP displays
  4/7 drm/edid: parse DSC DPP passthru support flag for mode validation
  5/7 drm/edid: for consistency, use mask everywhere for block parsing
  6/7 drm/edid: parse DRM VESA dsc bpp target
  7/7 drm/amd: use fixed dsc bits-per-pixel from edid

Optional: applied by default in the Rustlux PKGBUILD / Makefile, can be
disabled with _bigscreen_beyond=no (makepkg) or RUSTLUX_BSB=no (make).

